        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles west of Angola to near Clayton.
Movement was southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Angola, Bryan, Montpelier, Butler, Morenci, Fremont, Edgerton, West
Unity, Hamilton, Pioneer, Fayette, Reading, Edon, Holiday City,
Edgerton In Williams County, Columbia, West Jefferson, Ray, Cambria,
and Pulaski.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 340 and 357.
Interstate 69 in Michigan near mile marker 1.
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 139 and 156.
Interstate 80 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 35.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
